<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>



<head>



<title>TURN-RANDOMLY</title>

</head>



<body>
	<h3><i>I repeatedly turn left or right at most 15 degrees.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>TURN-RANDOMLY</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for maximum-left-turn -15  
substitute-text-area-for maximum-right-turn 15   
substitute-text-area-for cycle-duration 1                      
          
do-every cycle-duration
   [turn-right random-number-between maximum-left-turn maximum-right-turn]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>You can edit the contents of the text boxes to change the range of 
	angles. This uses a uniform random number distribution, you can use others. 
	You can change the frequency by changing the <i>1</i>.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="TURN-REPEATEDLY" href="TURN-REPEATEDLY.html">

	TURN-REPEATEDLY</a> turns a constant amount each tick.

	<a title="WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS" href="WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS.html">

	WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS</a> moves up, down, left, or right 

	rather than moving forward while turning a random amount. Together with

	<a title="MOVE-FORWARD" href="MOVE-FORWARD.html">

	MOVE-FORWARD</a> this will cause me to wander around.</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This schedules a rotation to occur every second. It randomly 

	choose a number between -15 and 15 as the amount of the object should turn.

	</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn.</p>
</body>
</html>

